WEBVTT

00:23.778 --> 00:24.921
Well good morning, how are we?

00:26.806 --> 00:36.050
It is good to be with you today and I want to say good morning to those of us joining us in the online community and those of you joining us in the classic service.

00:36.130 --> 00:41.154
glad that you guys are live with us this morning, worshiping and digging into the Word.

00:41.695 --> 00:43.616
If I haven't met you yet, my name is Doug.

00:43.637 --> 00:46.559
I'm one of the pastors here at Foot Hills and I would love to meet you.

00:46.579 --> 00:48.261
So come say hi, shake my hand.

00:48.801 --> 00:53.225
We've got a connect card in the chair pocket in front of you that you could fill out and just let us know that you are here.

00:53.805 --> 00:59.150
And we'll share a little bit about who we are and you can share a little bit about who you are and we can start this thing off right, okay?

00:59.570 --> 01:00.751
So please utilize that.

01:01.112 --> 01:02.913
If you've got your Bibles, please grab those.

01:02.973 --> 01:04.274
I'm gonna be in Isaiah 43.

01:04.915 --> 01:06.116
And if you wanna join me,

01:06.096 --> 01:14.366
We have a digital Bible app, then I'm gonna be using the ESV this morning so you can follow along in the same text that we are in.

01:14.426 --> 01:35.570
There are moments in life that will tend to feel insecure where maybe leadership will fail or an institution crumbles, maybe our plans that we've tried to muster up

01:36.162 --> 01:36.803
collapse.

01:38.926 --> 01:46.358
And what you assumed would hold steady, it starts to tremble and then it doesn't.

01:47.881 --> 01:54.712
And somewhere in that instability, a question will rise to the surface.

01:54.992 --> 01:56.454
And it might be very quiet.

01:56.475 --> 02:03.666
It might be not necessarily in defiance or anger, but it's the question that goes

02:04.898 --> 02:06.220
Where are you?

02:08.324 --> 02:09.707
Where are you, God?

02:12.652 --> 02:19.525
And the texts we're looking at this morning in Isaiah 43, it's actually speaking into a moment like that for the people of Israel.

02:20.627 --> 02:29.042
God's people were facing exile and their city had been threatened, their temple had been desecrated, their leadership was fully exposed,

02:29.122 --> 02:39.595
And once what defined them as stable was now collapsing, and it's into that instability that God's gonna speak through Isaiah 43 today.

02:40.175 --> 02:58.738
So join me in verse one, it starts this way, but now thus says the Lord, he who created you, O Jacob, he who formed you, O Israel, fear not,

02:58.882 --> 03:07.773
For I have redeemed you, I have called you by name, and you are mine."

03:08.955 --> 03:12.059
You might want to underline that you are mine.

03:12.079 --> 03:16.344
What a striking way to begin his message.

03:17.125 --> 03:20.830
There's no strategy for political expansion.

03:20.870 --> 03:23.794
There's no

03:23.874 --> 03:28.939
immediate correction that needs to be made by the Israelites, the followers of God.

03:29.600 --> 03:38.810
There isn't any sort of economic reform that God is calling the people to.

03:38.870 --> 03:47.860
Instead, He just says, I have redeemed you and you are mine.

03:49.481 --> 03:53.746
In the face of all the instability, of everything happening,

03:53.858 --> 03:57.643
with the people of Israel, he starts this way.

03:58.364 --> 04:02.850
He starts with what I would call a covenant grounding.

04:02.870 --> 04:12.784
Now real quick, we tend to throw around Christianese language like covenant, and I wanna make sure you're on board with me and know what I'm talking about when I say that.

04:12.824 --> 04:22.738
So when I say covenant, what I'm talking about is how God is binding himself to his people with promises that are rooted

04:22.914 --> 04:26.778
not in their performance, but in his character.

04:28.440 --> 04:32.624
So the one who's speaking is the creator and the sustainer of all that exists.

04:32.885 --> 04:37.690
He is the one who established covenant with Abraham and delivered them from Egypt.

04:37.990 --> 04:43.997
He speaks not as a distant deity, but as their covenant Lord.

04:45.919 --> 04:46.620
What does he say?

04:48.582 --> 04:49.182
Fear not.

04:50.784 --> 04:52.626
For I have redeemed you

04:53.538 --> 04:55.561
You are mine.

04:59.207 --> 05:10.986
This isn't him trying to tell the people to just muster up some emotional uplifting thoughts.

05:13.089 --> 05:16.455
No, this is deliverance language.

05:16.475 --> 05:18.598
This is ownership language.

05:18.658 --> 05:20.882
It's purchase language.

05:22.306 --> 05:24.990
He says, I have called you by name, I have.

05:25.972 --> 05:26.693
That's personal.

05:27.634 --> 05:31.561
And then if that's not personal enough, he goes, you are mine.

05:31.621 --> 05:47.666
Any trembling soul could be steadied and calmed at the reality that the one who spoke the world into being, the one who gives the breath of life goes, you are mine.

05:51.810 --> 06:01.445
Some of us know what it's like to grow up in an environment that's not steady, that doesn't have the protection that it should.

06:02.787 --> 06:09.117
To feel unseen or to feel like no one has stepped in or to feel like we were left.

06:09.257 --> 06:16.869
And when that's part of your story, you hear that you are mine and you see how it hits different.

06:17.951 --> 06:20.114
It doesn't land so religious.

06:21.506 --> 06:23.488
It sounds like rescue.

06:25.551 --> 06:27.473
And that's where the people of Israel were at.

06:30.097 --> 06:33.661
They weren't being told, you just need to perform better and Babylon will go away.

06:35.984 --> 06:39.789
You don't need to correct anything and then I'll smite them.

06:41.030 --> 06:42.052
You don't need to reform.

06:42.072 --> 06:43.894
You don't need to prove anything.

06:43.954 --> 06:47.999
He says, first and foremost, while you're in exile, I need you to understand something.

06:49.561 --> 06:50.482
You are mine.

06:54.338 --> 07:03.692
Really what he's pointing at in Isaiah 43 is that as Isaiah wants us to hear, I want you to look at what God has done.

07:03.713 --> 07:07.198
I want you to look at who God is.

07:07.218 --> 07:09.762
I want you to look at what he promises.

07:09.782 --> 07:11.685
Then I want you to lean into that.

07:13.448 --> 07:15.030
I want you to lean into that.

07:17.854 --> 07:22.802
In verse two, he says, when you pass through the waters, I'll be with you.

07:24.322 --> 07:26.605
And through the rivers, they shall not overwhelm you.

07:26.626 --> 07:31.333
And when you walk through fire, you shall not be burned, and the flame shall not consume you."

07:31.813 --> 07:34.157
I think it's so easy to read these passages.

07:34.718 --> 07:36.421
I was just talking to my son the other day.

07:36.721 --> 07:41.989
He's reading through the Bible, and he was telling me about what he was reading, and I said, just don't miss it.

07:43.692 --> 07:49.080
It's so easy for us to just read through something and go, yeah, it's a lot of repetition, or it's a lot of poetry.

07:49.921 --> 07:50.502
Slow down.

07:51.964 --> 07:53.106
What is he saying?

07:53.346 --> 07:55.990
This is one of the great imageries that we get.

07:56.090 --> 07:57.111
I absolutely love this.

07:57.211 --> 07:58.092
So a couple of reasons.

07:58.132 --> 07:59.995
First of all, look at what he's not saying.

08:01.076 --> 08:01.617
Look what he's not saying.

08:01.637 --> 08:09.788
He's not saying, hey, if you pass through the waters, let me guess when you pass through the waters.

08:11.370 --> 08:15.676
He doesn't say, I will keep you from all fire.

08:15.716 --> 08:23.346
He says, when you walk through fire, see friends, what he's getting at is that the promise

08:23.970 --> 08:25.814
is not absence of hardship.

08:26.877 --> 08:30.305
The promise is presence in hardship.

08:31.508 --> 08:32.450
That's incredible.

08:35.478 --> 08:39.307
For Isaiah's original audience, a language would have immediately stirred up some memories.

08:39.347 --> 08:41.031
Are you tracking with what the memories are?

08:41.713 --> 08:42.354
Are you there?

08:43.522 --> 08:50.273
When God separated the waters of the Red Sea in Exodus 14, He made a way for His people to walk through on dry ground.

08:50.293 --> 08:57.865
The Egyptians are closing in behind them and there's these walls of water put up on either side and Israel passes through the sea.

08:58.346 --> 09:03.634
Not because Israel is strong, not because they made a perfect sacrifice.

09:04.386 --> 09:06.990
Not because they repented before they went through.

09:07.550 --> 09:08.391
None of that.

09:08.692 --> 09:10.955
Instead, he says, I will redeem you.

09:11.015 --> 09:12.076
Let's go.

09:12.097 --> 09:17.624
They leave Egypt and he goes, I've got you covered and he moves the water.

09:20.488 --> 09:20.788
Why?

09:24.694 --> 09:25.595
Because you're mine.

09:27.217 --> 09:27.658
That's it.

09:28.899 --> 09:29.320
That's it.

09:29.460 --> 09:30.141
No condition.

09:33.065 --> 09:33.746
Incredible.

09:34.466 --> 09:39.895
And if that's not incredible, I mean, I think about the river.

09:39.955 --> 09:40.956
He talks about the river.

09:41.758 --> 09:43.480
Well, that's a throwback to Joshua 3.

09:44.242 --> 09:48.008
Joshua 3, the Israelites are trying to cross the Jordan River while it's at flood stage.

09:48.268 --> 09:49.029
It was impassable.

09:49.630 --> 09:54.338
And so again, God costs the waters to stand still so that they could walk through on dry ground.

09:57.162 --> 10:01.970
So when he's saying you're going to pass through the waters, he's not being poetic.

10:02.978 --> 10:16.296
He's actually recalling history, and he's reminding them that the God who made a way through the Red Sea, the God who stopped the Jordan River, that same God is still with you.

10:18.179 --> 10:20.222
And if that were not enough, I love this.

10:22.044 --> 10:23.346
You ever heard of Rackschach and Benny?

10:27.371 --> 10:32.178
He says, when you walk through the fire,

10:32.802 --> 10:34.346
You shall not be consumed.

10:35.870 --> 10:35.970
Huh?

10:37.454 --> 10:38.356
Can you tell anybody?

10:40.843 --> 10:42.226
You shall not be burned.

10:42.487 --> 10:43.730
This is incredible.

10:44.610 --> 11:00.187
So not only in the ancient world does a fire represent destruction, devastation, judgment, cities were burned, nations were burned, temples were burned, and Isaiah is preparing them for the reality that Jerusalem itself is gonna be burned, and this isn't a prophecy to Raxchach and Benny.

11:00.488 --> 11:13.522
However, if you're Raxchach and Benny and you're going, I remember that my God owns me, and that fire will not consume me, and so my identity is not Nebuchadnezzar, it's in my God, and then all of a sudden God redeems them.

11:14.114 --> 11:14.795
and saves them further.

11:14.815 --> 11:15.576
Is that amazing?

11:20.323 --> 11:26.272
What Isaiah is trying to get at friends is that these people belong to God.

11:27.754 --> 11:30.539
And because they belong to God, they will not be consumed.

11:32.041 --> 11:33.343
They will be protected.

11:33.383 --> 11:38.210
That's the thread that's holding this whole passage together.

11:40.053 --> 11:40.754
You are mine.

11:41.762 --> 11:43.245
The waters can't change that.

11:43.546 --> 11:45.831
The fires of life can't change that.

11:46.232 --> 11:48.577
Exile can't change that.

11:51.263 --> 11:54.349
I think that means something super deep in studying for you and me.

11:56.273 --> 11:58.418
You may walk through waters that feel overwhelming.

11:59.714 --> 12:16.332
You may feel like there are fires burning all around you, and the defining reality of your life is not the intensity of the waters, it's not the presence of the hardship, it's the identity given to you by God.

12:16.392 --> 12:19.115
I have redeemed you, you are mine.

12:19.155 --> 12:25.362
If you're sitting here as a believer in Jesus Christ, you've come to the realization that you are not God.

12:25.794 --> 12:42.720
that you have submitted yourself, you have recognized his kingship, that he alone is creator and sustainer, that he alone is the one who gives breath, you have recognized that he sent his son to die on a cross, to take your punishment for you, and then to cover you or atone you with his blood.

12:43.061 --> 12:50.693
If you have come to realize that, then friends, you've been purchased by the blood, and that means you are his.

12:50.753 --> 12:53.938
This is big.

12:55.202 --> 12:59.147
This is big, this is an identity transformation.

13:00.429 --> 13:02.892
You are no longer of this world.

13:03.874 --> 13:08.079
You're of the kingdom of God, which means the waters will not consume you.

13:10.022 --> 13:11.584
The fires will not consume you.

13:13.667 --> 13:17.392
He says, I, look at verse three.

13:17.833 --> 13:23.720
He goes, I am the Lord your God, the holy one of Israel.

13:23.740 --> 13:24.882
You wanna underline something else?

13:26.370 --> 13:27.392
Your savior.

13:29.915 --> 13:31.398
He's the savior.

13:34.582 --> 13:36.566
Look at what he says.

13:36.866 --> 13:39.129
I give Egypt as your ransom.

13:39.931 --> 13:41.854
Kush and see by an exchange for you.

13:42.034 --> 13:42.454
Why?

13:42.474 --> 13:44.057
I need you to hear this church.

13:44.217 --> 13:45.199
Open your ears and your eyes.

13:45.239 --> 13:52.329
I need you to see this because you are precious and honored.

13:52.650 --> 13:55.314
And he says, I love you.

13:56.674 --> 13:57.995
He says, I love you.

13:58.055 --> 14:09.346
Not because you've gotten it right, not because you're sinless, not because you're morally perfect, not because you give so much or you go to church so often, you serve in so many ministries.

14:09.707 --> 14:18.876
No, but because you are mine, you are precious to me and you are honored and I love you.

14:18.896 --> 14:21.518
Yes, is this not incredible?

14:22.720 --> 14:25.202
This blows my mind because who am I?

14:26.274 --> 14:28.156
In light of who he is, who am I?

14:28.196 --> 14:31.260
And yet he goes, I love you.

14:31.340 --> 14:34.364
This is covenant loyalty language, friends.

14:35.405 --> 14:43.515
This is the God of all that exists, the one who knit every cell together in not only your body, but in this world.

14:43.855 --> 14:46.839
And he is describing the people who belong to him.

14:46.879 --> 14:56.210
So if you belong to him, if you are a follower of Jesus who has been transformed and the spirit indwells you, he's talking about you.

14:58.178 --> 14:58.819
Big deal.

15:00.281 --> 15:01.702
Big, big deal.

15:01.742 --> 15:03.384
John Calvin says it like this.

15:03.464 --> 15:21.266
He says that when God calls Himself our Savior, He is testifying that He is the author of our safety so that we would not seek help anywhere else.

15:25.090 --> 15:28.453
This is what Isaiah is trying to describe for the Israelites.

15:28.473 --> 15:36.261
He's saying, God is cutting off every rival source of security.

15:37.362 --> 15:38.583
You need nothing else.

15:40.585 --> 15:41.586
Look at what God has done.

15:43.108 --> 15:44.329
Look at who he is.

15:44.709 --> 15:46.491
Look at what he promises.

15:46.932 --> 15:49.734
And now in response that we got to lean in.

15:51.977 --> 15:53.298
Look at verse five.

15:55.106 --> 15:57.670
Fear not for I am with you.

15:58.551 --> 15:59.713
These people were in exile.

16:00.514 --> 16:02.698
The Babylonian empire was terrifying.

16:04.000 --> 16:06.063
And he says fear not for I am with you.

16:06.083 --> 16:10.610
The repetition to what he said earlier in the first couple of verses is on purpose.

16:10.630 --> 16:14.856
See, the exile would tempt people to think that God had abandoned them.

16:16.158 --> 16:19.022
That their sin had exhausted his patience.

16:20.024 --> 16:24.050
That Babylon's gods were just more present and stronger.

16:24.866 --> 16:29.935
But the Holy One says, no, brah, I'm with you.

16:29.975 --> 16:32.781
I'm with you.

16:32.801 --> 16:40.615
Not because of anything you've done, not because you performed well, but because he formed them and redeemed them.

16:42.258 --> 16:45.885
Church, this is where dependence begins.

16:47.347 --> 16:48.850
It begins with your identity.

16:49.922 --> 16:55.890
You can't meaningfully lean into God until you know you belong to God.

16:57.091 --> 17:10.969
And leaning in here, when I'm talking about leaning in in this sense, what I'm saying is, it means like when the fears rise around you, when those insecurities rise, you don't rehearse what could go wrong or what you could do to fix it.

17:11.309 --> 17:18.098
Instead, you rehearse who he is and who you are.

17:18.914 --> 17:20.216
in light of who He is.

17:22.378 --> 17:24.121
That's what leaning in looks like.

17:25.322 --> 17:47.730
When we're feeling tempted to look for affirmation in our saviors, in our saviors, our money, our career that we've invested so much time and energy into, our saviors like our relationships, it's incredible how often we use people to be our saviors instead of God Himself.

17:48.834 --> 17:50.156
They complete me.

17:52.859 --> 17:53.099
Wow.

17:54.341 --> 17:55.662
That's rough if they complete you.

17:57.445 --> 17:58.065
But that's what we do.

17:58.105 --> 17:58.526
Is it not?

17:58.646 --> 17:59.247
Am I wrong?

17:59.928 --> 18:00.468
It's what we do.

18:02.070 --> 18:07.697
We lean on finite humans to make us feel good about ourselves, to give us our identity.

18:07.737 --> 18:08.478
We use careers.

18:08.498 --> 18:10.140
What is the first thing you ask when you meet somebody?

18:10.521 --> 18:11.041
So what do you do?

18:13.865 --> 18:14.866
Like that's who they are.

18:18.018 --> 18:22.305
We have all these saviors that we run to because they feel tangible.

18:23.387 --> 18:24.448
They feel practical.

18:25.310 --> 18:32.662
They give in in the moment feeling for us, but we're insatiable.

18:33.803 --> 18:40.695
And so we keep striving and we keep looking for the things of this world to comfort us, to give us an identity.

18:42.758 --> 18:45.362
When he goes, I've already identified you.

18:47.138 --> 18:51.683
I've already chosen you and redeemed you and called you by name.

18:51.703 --> 18:53.224
I formed you.

18:53.244 --> 18:56.187
You are mine."

19:00.932 --> 19:03.595
In verse eight, he shifts the tone.

19:03.615 --> 19:07.258
It actually becomes more courtroom-like conversation.

19:07.298 --> 19:12.363
He says, bring out the people who are blind, yet don't see.

19:12.404 --> 19:14.866
Those who hear

19:16.546 --> 19:17.287
But have ears.

19:18.689 --> 19:20.231
All the nations gather together.

19:20.271 --> 19:21.793
The people are to assemble.

19:22.874 --> 19:25.999
This is covenant courtroom language.

19:27.000 --> 19:28.863
He's summoning the nations before him.

19:29.283 --> 19:32.487
And what he's doing is he's challenging the false gods.

19:32.988 --> 19:36.393
He's asking questions that cut through the fog of the exile.

19:36.413 --> 19:36.973
Look at what he says.

19:36.993 --> 19:43.803
He goes, who among them, all the gathered nations, who among them can show us the former things.

19:44.243 --> 19:46.386
You know, Red Sea, all that stuff that he brought up.

19:47.394 --> 19:51.939
In other words, which of these gods, these Babylonian gods predicted history?

19:52.900 --> 19:55.603
And which of these idols can declare the future?

19:56.103 --> 19:57.905
Which of them can stand and testify?

19:57.925 --> 20:00.008
Then I love verse 10, it answers it for us.

20:01.970 --> 20:17.106
He goes, you are my witnesses and my servants whom I have chosen that you may know me and believe me and understand that I am he, God.

20:17.954 --> 20:25.246
Before me, no God was formed, nor after me, will there be any God.

20:26.688 --> 20:28.671
Friends, what a passage.

20:30.174 --> 20:36.564
He is making the bold, lettered, exclamation mark of monotheism.

20:37.806 --> 20:40.370
Before me, no God was formed, and there will be no God after me.

20:40.430 --> 20:45.298
So why are you searching for God's in your career and in your relationship?

20:45.442 --> 20:47.825
and with your money and with your time."

20:51.970 --> 20:52.431
I love it.

20:53.773 --> 20:54.714
He just hammers us.

20:54.734 --> 20:55.335
Look at verse 11.

20:55.355 --> 20:59.380
You know, you've probably heard countless times us go, when you hear something repeated, it's important, right?

20:59.400 --> 21:00.321
Well, look at verse 11.

21:01.763 --> 21:04.106
He goes, I pause.

21:06.189 --> 21:06.269
I.

21:07.851 --> 21:08.992
He's making a statement here.

21:09.032 --> 21:10.354
He's saying, I,

21:10.530 --> 21:11.972
I am the Lord.

21:12.153 --> 21:15.598
And besides me, there is no Savior.

21:15.658 --> 21:18.523
Wow.

21:20.867 --> 21:28.759
He's trying to hammer home for us that we need to stop looking outside of him for comfort and belonging and for identity.

21:28.799 --> 21:35.410
And instead notice him, see him, understand who he is and who we are in light of him.

21:38.018 --> 21:41.223
Just like us, the Babylonians were surrounded by alternative saviors.

21:42.284 --> 21:51.839
Political powers, cultural pressures, the temptation would be to hedge their bets on what feels tangible, what feels practical, what feels real in front of them.

21:53.521 --> 21:56.906
But God completely dismantles that possibility.

21:57.026 --> 21:58.569
He goes, besides me, there is no savior.

21:59.770 --> 22:04.818
There won't be any gods after me.

22:05.282 --> 22:08.105
In our day, you can even join a religion that says you'll be a God.

22:11.728 --> 22:12.229
Nothing new.

22:13.490 --> 22:14.511
Nothing new under the sun.

22:17.133 --> 22:25.001
Now, we don't bow before Babylonian statues, but we're not immune to these saviors.

22:26.482 --> 22:32.208
Whether it's our political outcomes, our reputation, our health, our control, those relationships.

22:33.489 --> 22:34.770
And I need you to know

22:34.882 --> 22:37.686
None of those things are evil in and of themselves.

22:40.069 --> 22:42.932
The problem is when those things take our priority.

22:42.952 --> 22:44.614
I mean, let's just be real for a moment.

22:45.155 --> 22:56.670
I think about the amount of time and energy we put into career, that we put into a relationship, that we put into our stocks, or our retirement, or into our hobbies, or into our whatever.

22:56.710 --> 23:03.378
And I compare that to the amount of time invested in our relationship with God.

23:06.146 --> 23:12.615
It reveals, friends, it reveals for us who we think the real Savior is.

23:12.655 --> 23:25.932
Isaiah is exposing this issue.

23:25.952 --> 23:29.377
He doesn't rant, he's not shaming, he's just letting God speak.

23:29.497 --> 23:33.202
He says it again, I, I am the Lord.

23:37.058 --> 23:51.425
Leaning in here, leaning into all of this means that when we are being discouraged or tempted, we don't lean on those lesser saviors.

23:52.106 --> 23:57.396
We refuse to give them authority in our lives because that belongs to God alone.

23:57.416 --> 23:58.578
Are you guys with me on this?

24:01.058 --> 24:03.040
We don't lean on ourselves.

24:03.060 --> 24:08.105
We don't lean on our careers or on our giftings or on our strengths or whatever.

24:08.145 --> 24:14.952
In our moment of instability, we go to our knees before God.

24:18.095 --> 24:19.997
He's the only one that can save us.

24:20.097 --> 24:21.959
He's the only one who can redeem us.

24:22.280 --> 24:28.466
He's the one who calls us his and so he shows us who he is.

24:29.986 --> 24:32.429
There's another shift in tone if you look at verse 14.

24:35.353 --> 24:37.435
This is, it gets good, man.

24:37.896 --> 24:38.877
Thus says the Lord.

24:39.478 --> 24:43.402
Your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel, he just keeps repeating this idea in case we haven't gotten it yet.

24:43.423 --> 24:51.993
Your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel, for your sake, I send a Babylon and bring all of them down as fugitives.

24:52.514 --> 24:54.176
So God's speaking directly to Babylon here.

24:54.576 --> 24:59.282
The empire that looked invincible, that looked permanent,

25:00.034 --> 25:04.059
that had swallowed Judah whole, God goes for your sake.

25:04.099 --> 25:06.141
See Babylon isn't ultimate.

25:07.123 --> 25:10.707
The empire is not sovereign and history isn't random.

25:10.967 --> 25:15.533
And so God is deliberately reminding them in verse 16 of the Exodus, look at this.

25:15.873 --> 25:22.681
Thus says the Lord who makes a way in the sea, a path in the mighty waters, check this out.

25:23.983 --> 25:29.970
He brings them back to the moment when there was no way forward, but God made one.

25:32.130 --> 25:36.295
With Pharaoh and his people at their backs, they're trapped.

25:37.736 --> 25:40.499
The Red Sea in front of them, there's nowhere to go but to death.

25:42.662 --> 25:46.206
But because of who they are, God said, watch this.

25:50.010 --> 25:53.154
Verse 18, I think is really funny after reading verse 16.

25:53.174 --> 25:53.534
Look at this.

25:55.817 --> 26:00.722
After reminding them of the Red Sea, he says, remember not the former things.

26:02.594 --> 26:05.781
Nor consider the things of, I know I just brought up the Red Sea, but forget about it.

26:08.167 --> 26:08.428
Why?

26:08.448 --> 26:09.991
He goes, behold.

26:11.114 --> 26:12.076
I'm doing a new thing.

26:13.459 --> 26:14.782
And now it springs forth.

26:14.963 --> 26:16.306
Do you not see it?

26:17.762 --> 26:19.664
He's not telling him to erase their history.

26:19.684 --> 26:21.406
He's not dismissing the exodus.

26:21.746 --> 26:24.389
He's not minimizing why he himself is done.

26:24.670 --> 26:25.771
But friends, check it out.

26:26.091 --> 26:33.820
He's saying, don't limit me to how I worked before, because the God who split the sea is not confined to yesterday's methods.

26:35.161 --> 26:36.723
No, he goes, I will make it.

26:36.743 --> 26:37.043
You see it?

26:37.063 --> 26:37.524
Look at it.

26:37.544 --> 26:39.206
I will make a way in the wilderness.

26:39.226 --> 26:42.690
And look at this, rivers in the desert, the impossible.

26:45.293 --> 26:46.514
Look at what God has done.

26:47.010 --> 26:50.954
Look at who He is, look at what He promises, and then we lean in.

26:51.014 --> 26:55.059
These things are true for us as well, guys.

26:56.821 --> 27:03.928
We know that there has been times in our lives where our Redeemer has stepped in, and He has moved, and He has made the impassable, passable.

27:07.512 --> 27:09.795
We have to stay grounded in that reality.

27:10.275 --> 27:16.402
We can't be distracted going, you know, our best days are behind us.

27:18.242 --> 27:23.354
We can't say, well, our failures have limited what God can do through us.

27:24.758 --> 27:27.124
Our story has already been written.

27:27.184 --> 27:30.191
Isaiah says, don't limit him.

27:30.412 --> 27:34.201
He's not confined to what he's done before.

27:34.562 --> 27:36.306
He's still redeeming.

27:38.498 --> 27:42.283
And when the, I love this, this is an amazing chapter, friends.

27:42.303 --> 27:45.608
You should spend this week just going over it and going over it and going over it.

27:46.009 --> 27:47.571
Look at verse 22, what he does.

27:47.651 --> 27:51.056
Again, there's this, when everything feels so triumphant, look what he says.

27:51.657 --> 27:52.678
He goes, isn't this great?

27:52.878 --> 27:53.499
I redeemed you.

27:53.559 --> 27:59.468
Hey, by the way, remember when you didn't call on me, but you have been weary of me?

28:00.689 --> 28:03.954
Remember how you have not brought me your sheep for burnt offerings?

28:04.482 --> 28:09.449
How you have burdened me with your sins, how you have wearied me with your iniquities.

28:09.850 --> 28:11.572
Oh, okay, it's getting real, it's getting personal.

28:13.115 --> 28:14.477
This was feeling good for a little bit.

28:15.939 --> 28:17.561
Now he's gonna tell us we need to change.

28:17.841 --> 28:19.925
Now he's gonna tell us how to do our sacrifices.

28:22.729 --> 28:23.770
He goes, you didn't call on me.

28:26.053 --> 28:26.955
And then look at verse 25.

28:27.155 --> 28:31.922
I pause.

28:33.314 --> 28:38.581
I am he who blots out your transgressions for whose sake?

28:39.002 --> 28:39.703
My sake.

28:41.045 --> 28:42.587
And I will not remember your sins.

28:44.830 --> 28:55.525
He doesn't go because you've improved or because you tried harder, because you prayed more, because you gave more, or because you've just leaned in just enough.

28:55.545 --> 28:58.069
You finally got victory over that one area.

28:58.089 --> 29:00.192
He goes, no, no, no, he goes, no, just for my sake.

29:00.933 --> 29:01.874
Friends, hear this.

29:02.274 --> 29:06.879
Forgiveness flows from God's character, not our performance.

29:11.584 --> 29:22.496
Got a text message yesterday from a student asking about, for a friend of his, just feeling the weight and guilt of his repeated sin.

29:23.537 --> 29:29.063
And doesn't God just take away our salvation as the son, these are my words, kind of summing up what the text was?

29:30.204 --> 29:31.986
And I'm like,

29:32.130 --> 29:40.182
Nabrah, Romans 8, 1, for there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.

29:42.866 --> 29:49.596
If you belong to the Father, he looks at you and he says, you are mine.

29:51.639 --> 29:54.824
John 10, 27, no one can snatch them out of the Father's hand.

29:54.844 --> 29:56.407
The Father has given them to me.

29:56.667 --> 29:58.570
The Father and I are one.

29:58.610 --> 30:01.394
No one can snatch them out of my hand.

30:02.850 --> 30:06.674
There is victory in this.

30:06.774 --> 30:15.262
If you're carrying shame or guilt, the weight of that, if I was just better, if I was just holier, if I was just, I mean, it's the stupid thing.

30:15.282 --> 30:17.304
Everybody goes, pastors are so good and so holy.

30:17.344 --> 30:18.045
Are you kidding me?

30:18.325 --> 30:19.546
Hang out with my wife for a day.

30:21.548 --> 30:23.450
You'll find out how broken I am, right?

30:23.490 --> 30:27.974
I'm not qualified because of me.

30:28.034 --> 30:29.335
I'm qualified because of him.

30:29.375 --> 30:32.178
And that's the same for you.

30:33.314 --> 30:38.259
You're not qualified to be a follower of Jesus because you don't cuss so much or you give so much or you serve.

30:38.600 --> 30:39.761
None of that matters to him.

30:40.502 --> 30:45.007
Isaiah 1, we talked about this weeks ago, he goes, all right, let's just settle the matter.

30:45.247 --> 30:45.667
You know what?

30:46.869 --> 30:47.449
Forget about it.

30:48.811 --> 30:50.312
I'm gonna make you as white as snow.

30:52.134 --> 30:55.258
That's why because you are his.

30:58.041 --> 31:03.186
So leaning in here, friends, looks like when you fail,

31:04.258 --> 31:07.002
You return quickly instead of hiding in a garden.

31:07.183 --> 31:07.603
You hear me?

31:10.448 --> 31:14.554
Because his mercy is grounded in his name, not in your consistency.

31:19.842 --> 31:20.924
That's covenant mercy.

31:21.845 --> 31:22.647
That's grace.

31:23.007 --> 31:25.451
That's why dependence is not desperation.

31:25.772 --> 31:27.314
It's alignment with reality.

31:28.866 --> 31:32.530
Isaiah 43 isn't calling us to some spiritual striving.

31:32.550 --> 31:35.534
It's calling us to spiritual dependency friends.

31:36.235 --> 31:37.296
You belong to him.

31:37.356 --> 31:38.758
There is no other savior.

31:38.958 --> 31:45.246
He does more than you even recognize or see and his grace runs deeper than our failures.

31:45.506 --> 31:47.829
So let's not live as though we've been abandoned.

31:47.849 --> 31:51.614
Let's not lean on these lesser saviors, these false religions.

31:52.234 --> 31:53.336
Ooh, you can be a God too.

31:53.916 --> 31:54.177
What?

31:56.960 --> 31:58.482
Let's not assume

31:58.978 --> 32:06.890
The story is finished because of what he did before, but let's recognize he's not confined to the past.

32:06.910 --> 32:08.232
He's gonna do a new thing in you.

32:10.375 --> 32:12.338
So live out the reality of your identity.

32:13.099 --> 32:14.361
Look at what God has done.

32:16.024 --> 32:22.293
Look at who he is and look at what he promises and then friends lean in.

32:25.157 --> 32:25.618
Let's pray.

32:27.938 --> 32:31.525
I want to just embrace that so badly, Jesus.

32:31.805 --> 32:40.020
There's so many days where I feel like it's on me, whether it's raising my children or performing in my career or my marriage.

32:40.061 --> 32:49.458
I feel like it is all on me and I don't mean to say I have no responsibility, but Jesus, the reality is I move in response to you, not apart from you.

32:50.082 --> 32:58.600
I move in response to you saying that I am yours and that you have redeemed me and it's out of that reality father that I want to live my life dependant fully on you.

32:58.620 --> 33:06.898
I want to lead and love my children and my spouse and move in my career out of the overflow of the work you've done in me, not my own self.

33:08.098 --> 33:10.283
And I pray that for the people in this room, Jesus.

33:10.663 --> 33:20.584
My prayer is that your spirit would move deeply within them and as they go throughout their week that Father, your spirit would prompt them and remind them of who they are.

33:20.604 --> 33:29.042
That they are precious and honored and that you love them so deeply, deeply enough.

33:30.082 --> 33:38.112
that you sent your son to die on a cross for them, to atone for them, to cover them, to take on their punishment.

33:38.452 --> 33:40.675
And Jesus, we get to live in the reality of that.

33:40.695 --> 33:44.620
And so as we move forward today, Father, would we move forward as grateful people?

33:45.922 --> 33:50.888
People recognizing and seeing you in the fires all around us.

33:53.872 --> 33:55.634
The Father, we would keep our eyes fixed.

33:56.770 --> 34:05.640
This world can be hard and it can be painful and it can be discouraging and it can be shiny and distracting.

34:08.483 --> 34:26.162
The Father here this morning in our right mind, we recognize who we are in light of who you are and we say thank you for adopting us, for grafting us in, for perching us,

34:26.530 --> 34:27.291
with your blood.

34:29.554 --> 34:29.955
Thank you.

34:31.016 --> 34:33.560
And so we live now, Jesus, in response to that.

34:34.241 --> 34:36.064
We live our lives as worship to you.

34:37.546 --> 34:40.410
Would it be a sweet and fragrant offering?

34:42.433 --> 34:44.896
We live to lift up your name, Jesus.

34:46.158 --> 34:47.480
All glory to you, Jesus.

34:47.700 --> 34:49.082
All honor and all praise.

34:50.024 --> 34:54.450
We cry out, holy, holy, holy with the host of angels.

34:56.354 --> 34:56.775
Amen.

35:00.199 --> 35:01.241
What a reality, man.

35:02.663 --> 35:07.249
I wish that when I'm not in my right mind, I could remember those things far easier.

35:08.250 --> 35:15.200
You know, it could be your thing this week is getting a piece of paper and writing, you are mine and putting it on your steering wheel right there.

35:15.660 --> 35:18.584
It could be maybe you write it on the mirror in your bathroom, you are mine.

35:18.624 --> 35:22.770
Maybe there's just some things that you need to do this week to keep that at the forefront of your thoughts.

35:23.586 --> 35:25.228
that you are his, that you are redeemed.

35:25.248 --> 35:26.310
Maybe just write redeemed.

35:27.551 --> 35:29.955
Maybe tattoo on the bottom of your big toe, redeemed.

35:30.335 --> 35:31.777
I don't know, something.

35:33.600 --> 35:34.781
We just got to keep it there, man.

35:34.801 --> 35:36.023
We just got to keep it at the forefront.

35:36.303 --> 35:40.549
Hey, I hope you have a fantastic week pursuing Jesus leaning in.

35:40.990 --> 35:45.095
You may have noticed that the student missionaries are out on the patio.

35:45.496 --> 35:48.820
They are raising funds to go preach the gospel to Croatia.

35:49.561 --> 35:53.106
We have been working hard over the last several years to build trust.

35:53.378 --> 36:02.610
to build relationship, to build the foundation so that more and more Croatian young people can come to know Jesus in a country where less than 1% know Jesus.

36:03.651 --> 36:09.098
By the grace of God, they hadn't seen any salvation in over 10 years and in the last two years we've seen three.

36:10.039 --> 36:16.368
Our hope is that our work would be fruitful because the harvest is plentiful and there's a few laborers willing to head over there.

36:16.828 --> 36:21.394
If you're willing to support them financially and through prayer we want to know,

36:21.474 --> 36:23.060
The wall, if you're like, what is this?

36:23.080 --> 36:23.722
How does it work?

36:23.802 --> 36:28.600
Basically, there's an envelope on there that they decorated that has a number on it, and a dollar amount.

36:29.001 --> 36:30.386
If you take that envelope,

36:30.466 --> 36:33.690
You're declaring, I'm going to give this much to support this mission.

36:34.150 --> 36:36.513
And so I just ask that you follow the slip inside.

36:37.033 --> 36:40.217
You can give online through Venmo, check, cash, whatever.

36:40.777 --> 36:44.201
But if you take an envelope, that's a commitment saying, we've got you.

36:44.221 --> 36:45.803
We're going to support you and make this happen.

36:46.243 --> 36:49.507
So please, if you will, go support our missionaries.

36:49.527 --> 36:50.328
Ask them questions.

36:50.348 --> 36:51.629
You'll see them all over the patio.

36:52.510 --> 36:57.275
Ask them about what their mission is, how excited they are, what they're worried about, any of those things.

36:58.116 --> 36:59.858
But let's go love them and support them well.

37:00.354 --> 37:01.218
God bless you, friends.

37:01.379 --> 37:06.482
If you came ready to tithe, boxes are in the back, otherwise you can give online, and we'll see you on Sunday.

